A food product deriving primarily from corn (maize).
A food product consisting of an edible fungi or mushroom or yeast.
A fungus food product which has yeast as its primary and defining ingredient.
A food product derived from one or more microorganisms including bacteria, mold, and yeast.
A food product derived from or produced by a plant root.
A potato food product is any product derived from potatoes.
Food items that are rich in sugar, any one or type of which is called a confection. Modern usage may include substances rich in artificial sweeteners as well.

A citrus fruit is botanically classified as a type of berry called a hesperidium that has a thick, leathery rind, with numerous oil glands, and a large flesh portion composed of several wedge-shaped sections. Unlike pome fruit, such as the apple, the citrus fruit is derived from a superior ovary, an ovary completely separate from the calyx.
The fleshy fruit (false berry) of a plant of the family Cucurbitaceae.

Citrullus lanatus is a plant species in the family Cucurbitaceae, a vine-like (scrambler and trailer) flowering plant originally from sub-Saharan Africa. It is cultivated for its fruit. The subdivision of this species into two varieties, watermelons (Citrullus lanatus (Thunb.) var. lanatus) and citron melons (Citrullus lanatus var. citroides (L. H. Bailey) Mansf.)
A food product deriving from one or more tomatoes.
A food product with insects as a defining ingredient.

Food product that is 1) ready or nearly ready for consumption; 2) usually a composite of several foods or ingredients that often belong to distinct product types; 3) usually formulated, mixed and partially or fully cooked.
A food product which is an output of a food cooking process.
A staple food prepared from a dough of flour (usually wheat) and water, usually by baking
This food product type includes food products which are derived from a large, diverse group of photosynthetic organisms.
A food product made from oats.
